# Wistia Video Embedding

When embedding Wistia videos in Docusaurus documentation files, use the following format:

```mdx
<div
  className="wistia_responsive_padding"
  style={{ padding: '56.25% 0 0 0', position: 'relative' }}
>
  <div
    className="wistia_responsive_wrapper"
    style={{ height: '100%', left: 0, position: 'absolute', top: 0, width: '100%' }}
  >
    <iframe
      src="https://fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/{VIDEO_ID}?web_component=true&seo=true"
      title="{Descriptive Video Title}"
      allow="autoplay; fullscreen"
      allowTransparency
      frameBorder="0"
      scrolling="no"
      className="wistia_embed"
      name="wistia_embed"
      width="100%"
      height="100%"
    ></iframe>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="https://fast.wistia.net/player.js" async></script>
```

## Requirements:
- Files must be `.mdx` (not `.md`) to support JSX/HTML. If working with a `.md` file, convert it to `.mdx` first.
- Replace `{VIDEO_ID}` with the actual Wistia media ID (e.g., `stb74pd0qz`)
- Replace `{Descriptive Video Title}` with a descriptive, accessible title
- The script tag must be included after the div wrapper
- Use this exact structure - do not create custom components for Wistia embeds
- Applies to all Docusaurus documentation files in `docusaurus/docs/**/*.{md,mdx}`

